# Eoilinhtinh — Cursor AI Rules
# Interactive 3D Lamp Kiosk · Next.js + MediaPipe + React Three Fiber
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These rules enforce the performance and UX contracts that keep the
# kiosk at 60 fps on a single-board event PC with no mouse/keyboard.
# Read them before touching any file in this repo.

## THREAD SAFETY — NEVER VIOLATE

- ALL MediaPipe inference lives in `src/workers/handTracking.worker.ts`.
  NEVER import HandLandmarker, FilesetResolver, or any @mediapipe/* into
  a React component or hook on the main thread.

- The worker communicates via a SINGLE `postMessage` round-trip per frame.
  NEVER add synchronous cross-thread calls or SharedArrayBuffer patterns.

- `useHandStore` is written ONLY by the worker result handler in
  `useHandWorker.ts`. NO component calls `useHandStore.setState()` directly.

- Inside `useFrame()` callbacks, ALWAYS read Zustand state via `getState()`:
    const { leftHand, rightHand } = useHandStore.getState();   // correct
    const { leftHand } = useHandStore();                       // WRONG — re-renders every frame

- NEVER call `useState` or `useReducer` for data that updates every frame.
  Use `useRef` for mutable frame-rate values (rotation delta, zoom, etc.).

## ZERO RE-RENDER CONTRACT

- `useHandStore.setState()` MUST be called with the same object shape it was
  initialised with. Adding new keys to the frame-rate store is forbidden — use
  a separate Zustand slice for application state.

- `useGalleryStore` (lamp navigation, isGrabbing, isSelected) is the only
  store that React components may subscribe to. Subscribe with selectors:
    useGalleryStore((s) => s.activeLampIndex)   // correct — only re-renders on index change
    useGalleryStore()                            // WRONG — re-renders on ANY store mutation

- `useTutorialStore` follows the same selector rule.

## GESTURE MATH — PURE FUNCTIONS ONLY

- `src/lib/gestures.ts` MUST remain a pure math module: no React, no Zustand,
  no side effects, no DOM access.

- Every gesture measurement MUST be divided by `handSize(landmarks)` before
  comparison with a threshold. Raw pixel or normalized coordinates are NOT
  distance-invariant and will fail at 1.5 m standing distance.

- `grabConfidence()` returns a continuous 0–1 float. NEVER threshold it to
  a boolean before storing — the glow shader needs the continuous value.

- `detectSwipe()` requires BOTH displacement ≥ 0.22 AND velocity ≥ 0.0008/ms.
  Do not weaken either threshold; false swipes disrupt the 1.5 m user experience.

## THREE.JS / R3F PERFORMANCE

- The Canvas MUST have `flat={true}`. Without it, ACESFilmic tone-mapping
  clamps emissiveIntensity > 1.0 and Bloom has no effect.

- NEVER read `.boundingSphere` without calling `geometry.computeBoundingSphere()`
  first. STL files do not pre-compute it.

- NEVER call `geometry.computeVertexNormals()` inside a `useFrame` callback.
  Call it once inside `useMemo` when the geometry first loads.

- `THREE.MathUtils.damp(current, target, lambda, delta)` is mandatory for ALL
  animated values. NEVER use `lerp(a, b, 0.1)` with a fixed coefficient — it
  is frame-rate dependent and will judder at non-60fps.

- `key={modelUrl}` on the `<Suspense>` boundary is required for model hot-swap.
  Removing it causes the old geometry to persist and the new one to overlay it.

- Bloom post-process settings are locked: luminanceThreshold 0.18, intensity 1.8,
  KernelSize.LARGE, blendFunction ADD, mipmapBlur true.
  Do not change these without testing at the event venue lighting conditions.

## STL PIPELINE

- STL files carry ZERO material data. ALWAYS inject a `<meshStandardMaterial>`
  manually in the LampSTLMesh component.

- Auto-scale formula: `TARGET_WORLD_SIZE / (boundingSphere.radius * 2)` where
  `TARGET_WORLD_SIZE = 3.2`. Do not hard-code per-model scale values.

- NEVER use `<primitive object={geometry} />` for STL — always compose as
  `<mesh><bufferGeometry /><meshStandardMaterial /></mesh>`.

## UPLOAD / CMS

- `src/app/actions/uploadModel.ts` is a Next.js Server Action (`'use server'`).
  NEVER call Vercel Blob `put()` from a client component or API route.

- The five validation layers MUST run in order: File instance check →
  extension check → size check → magic-byte sniff → filename sanitize.
  Do not reorder or skip any layer.

- `addRandomSuffix: false` is intentional — the timestamp prefix already
  prevents collisions. Do not remove it.

## TYPOGRAPHY — 1.5 M OUTDOOR RULE

- Minimum body text: `text-xl` (20 px). This is a hard floor for anything
  a standing user 1–1.5 m away must read.

- Lamp names: `text-7xl font-black`. Do not downsize "to fit" — truncate
  the string instead if it overflows.

- Taglines: `text-3xl font-bold` minimum.
- Descriptions: `text-2xl font-semibold` minimum.
- Gesture hint icons: minimum 56 × 56 px rendered size (w-14 h-14).

## SAFE ZONE — NO BOTTOM UI

- NOTHING interactive or critical may be placed in the bottom 20% of the
  screen (below `bottom-[20vh]`). The bottom edge is unreachable at the
  event PC's height and viewing distance.

- All fixed UI must use `top-*`, `left-*`, `right-*`, or vertical centering
  with `top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2`. The `bottom-*` utility is BANNED for
  permanent elements.

- The Skip button in TutorialOverlay is `fixed top-10 right-10`.
  Do not move it.

## WASM ASSETS

- MediaPipe WASM files are served from `/public/mediapipe/` as static assets.
  They CANNOT be processed by webpack. NEVER import them — reference via URL string.

- The worker resolves the base path as:
    const wasmBasePath = '/mediapipe';
  Do not use relative paths or dynamic `import.meta.url` tricks inside workers.

## NAMING AND FILE PLACEMENT

- Gesture bridge logic → `src/hooks/useGestureDetector.ts` only.
- Raw landmark store → `src/store/useHandStore.ts` only.
- Gallery/nav state → `src/store/useGalleryStore.ts` only.
- Tutorial state → `src/store/useTutorialStore.ts` only.
- Pure gesture math → `src/lib/gestures.ts` only.
- Do NOT create additional stores, hooks, or math utilities without discussion.

## FORBIDDEN PATTERNS

```typescript
// BANNED — frame-rate subscriber
const { leftHand } = useHandStore();

// BANNED — lerp with fixed coefficient
mesh.rotation.y = THREE.MathUtils.lerp(mesh.rotation.y, target, 0.05);

// BANNED — MediaPipe on main thread
import { HandLandmarker } from '@mediapipe/tasks-vision';

// BANNED — UI at bottom
className="fixed bottom-10 right-10"

// BANNED — raw coordinate threshold (not normalized by handSize)
if (dist3(landmarks[8], landmarks[4]) < 0.08) { /* grab */ }

// BANNED — geometry mutation in useFrame
geometry.computeVertexNormals(); // inside useFrame callback
```
